%N A387494 Array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the maximum number of steps in a n^k cuboid with a rule that allows moving to neighboring visited cuboids if the next step is onto an unvisited cuboid when starting in a corner.
%C A387494 There are 2 step patterns, those being: unvisited -> visited -> unvisited, unvisited -> unvisited.
%F A387494 T(1, k) = 0.
%F A387494 T(n, 1) = n - 1.
%F A387494 T(n, 2) = 2*n*(n-1) = A046092(n-1).
%F A387494 Conjecture for n > 1: T(n, 3) = 2*n^3 - 3*n + floor(3/n).
%F A387494 Conjecture for general T(n, k) where delta(P) is the Kronecker delta (1 if P is true, 0 if P is false): delta(k != 0)*delta(n > 1)*(2*n^k - k*n + floor(k/n) - delta(k == 1) - delta(n == 2)*delta(k == 2)).
